cuems-wsclient (0.2.1-1) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * bridge: fix auto-load editor-success race that logged a false failure
    when the editor's project_ready ack returned before wait_engine's first
    sleep cycle (167868c). Three races in a row would have wrongly disabled
    auto-load for the session.
  * bridge: add controller_poweroff_cmd config field, optional split of the
    local controller's poweroff/reboot command from the SSH node command
    (f4c2304). Empty default preserves existing single-cmd behaviour; useful
    for safe testing when controller WoL-from-S5 is unreliable, and for
    maintenance reboots that should leave nodes powered off.
  * End-to-end verified against a real Shelly Pro 1 (`source: "timer"`
    proves hardware fired autonomously); SSH-fanout to slave_dev real
    (rc=0), reachability poll detected slave's network-down at +14s, then
    Shelly armed and local poweroff issued at +16s.

 -- Ion Reguera <ion@stagelab.coop>  Fri, 29 May 2026 19:20:00 +0200

cuems-wsclient (0.2.0-1) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian packaging (dh-virtualenv); produces cuems-power-bridge.
  * Restructure repo to src/cuemswsclient/ layout; modernise wsclient.py
    + osclistener.py with license headers (kept for backwards compat).
  * New cuems-power-bridge daemon: HTTP server on :8478 that coordinates
    orderly cluster shutdown for the Shelly Pro 1 flip-switch and the
    Bitfocus Companion shutdown button. Single coordinator, asyncio.Lock
    against double-trigger.
  * Bridge maintains two persistent WebSocket connections (engine binary
    OSC on :9190, editor JSON on :9092) — engine connection drives the
    /engine/status/* cache used for refuse_if_running, editor connection
    drives the auto-load project_ready path.
  * Shutdown flow: refuse if project running → SSH-fanout poweroff to
    every NodeType.slave from network_map.xml → reachability poll until
    all nodes silent → arm Shelly hardware safety timer (Switch.Set
    on=true toggle_after=N) → local systemctl poweroff --no-block. Real
    orderly shutdown; mains drops on an already-off box.
  * Bridge exposes POST /go and POST /stop as thin HTTP→WebSocket-OSC
    proxies for Bitfocus Companion, since Companion's OSC module is
    UDP/TCP, not WebSocket-OSC. 200 ms per-endpoint rate-limit.
  * Auto-load on boot via editor's project_ready action (matches
    wsclient.py's proven pattern). auto_load_persistent flag for
    unattended installations; fail-fast on bad UUID via editor's error
    frame; auto-load disabled after 3 consecutive failures.
  * Configurable safety bounds: shelly_safety_timer_s validated 45..300s
    at startup; dry_run mode logs side-effects without executing.
  * Ships Shelly mJS template at /usr/share/cuems/shelly-mjs/cuems-
    shutdown.js; operator helper cuems-power-bridge-deploy-keys
    distributes the SSH pubkey to every node's authorized_keys.
  * Console entry points: cuems-power-bridge, cuems-power-bridge-deploy-
    keys, cuems-wsclient (legacy CLI).

 -- Ion Reguera <ion@stagelab.coop>  Wed, 27 May 2026 14:30:00 +0200
